  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "If you are using the \"pragma\" setting while compiling, Truffle will fail unhelpfully if a \"direct source\" (one supplied by the user in their `contracts` directory) does not contain a pragma expression. The error is something like \r\n```\r\nTypeError: Cannot read properties of null (reading '1')\r\nat getSemverExpression (/usr/local/lib/node_modules/truffle/build/webpack:/packages/compile-solidity/dist/compileWithPragmaAnalysis.js:19:46)\r\n```\r\n\r\nTruffle should error, explaining to the user that their \"direct sources\" must contain pragma expressions while using this setting.",
